First Gen Reports $13.3 Million Loss Due to Impairment Charge

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 
2011-08-15T00:47:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-15/first-gen-reports-13-3-million-loss-due-to-impairment-charge.html
First Gen Corp. (FGEN)  said it posted a net
loss of $13.3 million in the first half of the year due to an
impairment charge of unit  Energy Development Corp. (EDC)   The 5 billion pesos impairment charge for Northern Negros
Geothermal Power Plant was a “non-cash loss” resulting from
the decommissioning of the 49-megawatt power plant, First Gen
said in a disclosure to the stock exchange today.  A unit that operates a hydroelectric power plant complex
also reported lower revenue due to limited water availability
and lower electricity prices in the spot market, First Gen said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Cecilia Yap at 
 cyap19@bloomberg.net  